===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An item of [[furniture]] used to sit on or in comprising a [[seat]], legs, back, and sometimes arm rests, for use by one person. Compare [[stool]], [[couch]], [[sofa]], [[settee]], [[loveseat]] and [[bench]].
#* {{quote-book|year=1918|author={{w|W. B. Maxwell}}|chapter=12
|title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL1097634W The Mirror and the Lamp]
|passage=There were many wooden '''chairs''' for the bulk of his visitors, and two wicker arm'''chairs''' with red cloth cushions for superior people. From the packing-cases had emerged some Indian clubs,&nbsp;[…], and all these articles&nbsp;[…] made a scattered and untidy decoration that Mrs. Clough assiduously dusted and greatly cherished.}}
#* {{quote-book|year=1963|author={{w|Margery Allingham}}|title={{w|The China Governess}}
|chapter=19|url=http://openlibrary.org/works/OL2004261W
|passage=Meanwhile Nanny Broome was recovering from her initial panic and seemed anxious to make up for any kudos she might have lost, by exerting her personality to the utmost. She took the policeman's helmet and placed it on a '''chair''', and unfolded his tunic to shake it and fold it up again for him.}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|All I need to weather a snowstorm is hot coffee, a warm fire, a good book and a comfortable '''chair'''.}}
# [[chairperson|Chairperson]].
#* {{quote-book|year=1658-9|date=March 23|author=Thomas Burton|title=Diary
|passage=The '''Chair''' behaves himself like a Busby amongst so many school-boys{{...}}and takes a little too much on him.}}
#* {{quote-news|year=1887|date=September 5|work=The Times
|passage=It can hardly be conceived that the '''Chair''' would fail to gain the support of the House.}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|Under the rules of order adopted by the board, the '''chair''' may neither make nor second motions.}}
# {{context|music|lang=en}} The seating position of a particular musician in an orchestra.
#: {{usex|lang=en|My violin teacher used to play first '''chair''' with the Boston Pops.}}
# {{context|rail transport|lang=en}} Blocks that support and hold [[railroad]] track in position, and similar devices.
# {{context|chemistry|lang=en}} One of two possible [[conformer]]s of [[cyclohexane]] rings (the other being [[boat]]), shaped roughly like a chair.
# {{context|slang|with ''the''|lang=en}} The [[electric chair]].
#: {{usex|lang=en|He killed a cop: he's going to get the '''chair'''.}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|The court will show no mercy; if he gets convicted, it's the '''chair''' for him.}}
# A [[distinguished]] [[professorship]] at a university.
# An [[iron]] [[block]] used on [[railway]]s to support the [[rail]]s and secure them to the [[sleeper]]s.
# A [[vehicle]] for one person; either a [[sedan]] borne upon poles, or a two-wheeled carriage drawn by one horse; a [[gig]].
#: {{rfquotek|Shakespeare}}
#* {{w|Alexander Pope}}
#*: Think what an equipage thou hast in air, / And view with scorn two pages and a '''chair'''.

